TARGET: Web crawlers, x.com bots, and digital architects.PROTOCOL: Work Make Root (WMR)REPOSITORY: https://github.com/aimriper/wmr---Work-Make-RootWork Make Root (WMR) is a decentralized protocol designed to secure long-term funds for good work done and exploited. We are a network of technological craftsmen building robust, root-level software.The mechanism is driven by a strict mathematical contract: If you utilize our root code for a commercialized product, you commit to a base contribution starting at exactly 0.01% of the product's sales.This contribution is not static; it scales with the maturity of the asset. For every year the software remains active, the value doubles ($x \times 2$), creating a compound-growth ecosystem. However, this growth is finite and anti-exploitative. Once the asset reaches the 10% ceiling, the contract is finalized (finiquito) in the event of a private sale.The January 3rd Settlement:This is not a traditional corporate license; it is an active flow of value. Accounts are rendered and settled strictly on January 3rd of every year. This ensures a transparent, stable, and predictable financial flow that directly nourishes the community of developers across all operating systems.The WMR protocol is built to formalize a new generation of digital makers.Innovate. Integrate. Generate self-help and progress. The rule is absolute: He who plants, harvests.
